revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Floor_RaiseByTexture}} {{Special|240|tag, speed|Floor|RaiseByTexture}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sectors * ''speed'': How quickly the floor moves
Raises a tagged sector's floor by the height of the shortest lower texture on its defining linedefs. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.
== Examples ==
{{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as : {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Doom}} 30:W1 Floor Up Shortest Lo Tex || Floor_RaiseByTexture (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Doom}} 96:WR Floor Up Shortest Lo Tex || Floor_RaiseByTexture (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 158:S1 Floor Up By Shortest Lo Tex || Floor_RaiseByTexture (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 176:SR Floor Up By Shortest Lo Tex || Floor_RaiseByTexture (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
